I am very angry and disappointed I wasted my money for some trash food. Please make better quality food. It’s a shame to sell this type(quality)  of food to your community. I ordered ndole and it was the nastiest thing I have ever tasted. The food tasted as if it had been refrigerated for years. And the meat was overcooked and tasted rotten. The jamajama tasted rotten. Unfortunately I had no cars to take the food back to them, since I was just visiting. Make better food for your community. I don’t usually leave bad reviews on black businesses because I know we are all trying and have to lift one another up, but this was ridiculously disgusting.

The goat peanut stew was fantastic, and they give you portions plenty large enough. The guy I talked to who took my order, who I assume was Roger himself, had great manners and had lots to say about the items on the menu.
all the food was delicious --- we ordered take out to eat at home with friends - social distance.  Especially like the grill and the jolloff rice.

I got food today and there was a misunderstanding about one of the menu items. The food is always good. Just be sure when you order something to ask how it's prepared if you're not of African descent.
Nice restaurant

Owner Patrick, treats his customers like family..the food has been consistently delicious..well prepared & cooked to order. Roasted Tilapia with Jellof Rice and the House Veg... spinach. Not fast food call ahead so order is prepared with little or no wait at a reasonable price! Expect DELICIOUSNESS!😊🥰
Very delicious food. Got the beef grill with rice and vegetables. Very well seasoned and tender!

I go to silver springs about twice a year and Roger Miller's is always a place I make sure to go. This is a great little hidden gem and I highly recommend it. Make sure to get the fufu when you do go.
Food was ok. Service was amazing. We were treated like royalties. That little space outside would be fun in summertime.

Last week was our first time we went to this place. But It is definitely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening a lot with the courteous service, with the great  dishes and fine drinks and with the comfortable price. We will surely come back soon.

I enjoy coming here. I like the variety of West African dishes available. The service is always great and the staff is friendly. I'm picky about my Egusi but this place hits the spot. This is a long time relic in Silver Spring and I think this spot deserves to stick around. If you're ever in the area, definitely check it out.

The food was delicious and the owner made me feel like I was his own daughter. We drove down from Pennsylvania and he gave us free snacks for the ride home. It was such a wonderful experience. I can't wait to go back.

This is not much of a place if you're looking for ambiance bit if you're looking for delicious authentic african cuisine and a friendly staff this is the place. We got a huge order a little of everything and nothing disappointed.  I even got a call from the owner later that night just to make sure our meal was up to par. Good on ya roger miller!

See below initial review, and response from the owner:  “Terrible service. Twice now we have ordered goat from them, and they gave us beef, or have demanded we pay them more for goat, AFTER we had already paid. We also had 2 orders of wings this last time, and they sent only 1. I doubt we will order from them again, very disappointing. Oh and if you order online or on the phone, expect them to always be late.  Response from the owner a day ago Dear Joseph, I'm so sorry you had this terrible experience. This is not what we stand for. I can't believe this has happened twice. Something is not right. Any chance the person you're talking didn't understand what you ordered? Regardless, this is not acceptable. Please call and ask to speak to the Manager.”  I placed both orders online. Not over the phone, so there was no confusion on what I ordered. The first time you called me AFTER I had ordered AND paid, to tell me if I didn’t give you more money, you were going to swap out the goat with beef. The second time, you just swapped the goat out, without so much as a warning. You missed an entire order of wings the second time, and after I wrote that first review I ended up cracking a tooth on one of the wings.

The food was delicious, authentic, great size potions, and reasonable prices. Will definitely come here again.

Love it! I always get food when I can. I hate that they sell their suya per stick and it is 1 stick for $3.00 with 3 pieces of suya so 1 piece of meat for $1.00! If there was a place closer I would have gone. The customer service is good tho' and they are really nice.

Anthony Bourdain could easily feature this place on one of his shows. It's a casual, unassuming joint that serves true home cooked West African cuisine. My husband's cousin's husband (how confusing is that?) is from Cameroon and loves this place. We'd have never thought to try it without his recommendation. I was blown away by the roasted tilapia I ordered - they serve the entire fish! My husband ordered goat ndolle and it was equally delicious. Definitely, definitely eat here. We're looking forward to returning!

An excellent restaurant!  The food is superb.  I have taken one star away because the restaurant is small and cramped, but this should in no way deter you from enjoying the hospitality and food of this unique place. I have been there twice and thoroughly enjoyed myself both times.  All the food is good, but I do caution that  the bitter leaf dishes are, at least for me, an acquired taste. Highly recommended.
Ordered for a specific time for pick up.  They didn't have it ready even though I told 3 different people beforehand that I needed it at that time.

I was excited to try out this African restaurant and was excited to see it was a black owned business. I went on three separate occasions and today will be the last time I purchase anything from this restaurant. I called and placed my order and the woman over the phone told me it would be ready in 15 minutes. I got there 15 minuets later greeted the three men who were sitting there and was ignored (no big deal). I went up to the cash register where I greeted the woman. On the website the food I ordered was priced at 8.99 she told me me it was 9.99 and didn't adjust the price as it was advertised online (no big deal just 1$). I sat there and a Caucasian young man walked in instantly the owner who had just previously ignored me jumped out of his seat welcomed him offered him water and a table to sit at. (hmmmm) After tending to one of his more valuable customers I think he felt guilty and decided to come over to me and say "God bless you". I appreciate the food I ordered from here and the blessings he offered me I'm also happy I was able to support a black owned business but Ill think Ill spend my money where all customers are welcomed with the same amount of hospitality.
The server was very nice but the food has no taste. The food didn't look good or taste good. Worst food I ever ate.
Live music, generous portions, delicious chicken, great sauce, friendly owner.

My first time trying West African food in the area. Yummy, but I wasn'tused to the intense flavor of the bitter leaves dish. However, Jollof rice and fried wings were super good! I'll be back for more!
Tasty food for cheap. I tried the plantains and engussi stew. Everyone else I dined with enjoyed their meal too! Ambiance is nonexistent, but it's clean and cute.

This was my very first time trying African food so it didn't look great to me but it was soooooo good. I only spent $10 & some change. It's very cozy inside, nice atmosphere. But for some reason the waitress/server kept saying that she couldn't understand what I was saying. Then I realized there was no fufu in my bag after I left, which I really wanted to try. I would recommend trying the place out for yourself

the Yassa chicken was amazing and fried plantain to die for...didn't have to wait long for my food either....people here are very polite and amazing as well....would definitely be coming here again!

I am a regular at this neighborhood jewel. It's a cozy spot with a lot of character!  The food is very affordable with most of the dishes being under $15. When I am craving a home-cooked meal and don't feel like cooking, I go here. I've had the jollof rice, limbe beef, roasted fish, sautéed spinach, fufu, and I'm sure several other dishes. The food is always fresh and served hot. Mr. Patrick and his staff are awesome hosts. I highly encourage a visit to Roger Miller. #CityExperts
